WEBVTT

00:02.168 --> 00:04.129
- [gasps]
You're one of them.

00:04.212 --> 00:05.463
Stay back!

00:07.257 --> 00:08.591
- Don't worry.

00:08.675 --> 00:12.095
I'm not gonna hurt you.

00:12.178 --> 00:14.097
I'm gonna recruit you.

00:14.180 --> 00:15.598
- To do what?

00:15.682 --> 00:18.143
- To be my most
devout follower.

00:18.226 --> 00:20.228
Oh, I always wanted a minion.

00:20.311 --> 00:21.938
- I'll never follow you.

00:22.021 --> 00:23.064
- Your magic exposé
will never be.

00:23.148 --> 00:26.067
And you will be
loyal to only me.

00:27.861 --> 00:30.864
[laughing]

00:32.741 --> 00:34.409
No use running.

00:37.579 --> 00:39.998
Told ya.

00:50.175 --> 00:52.677
Are you my minion?

00:54.053 --> 00:55.638
- Yes, Mrs. Desdemona.

00:55.722 --> 00:57.307
And I can't wait to report
about it on <i>Miss Information.</i>

00:57.390 --> 00:58.308
- What?

00:58.391 --> 01:00.643
No.

01:03.438 --> 01:04.605
You're my minion.

01:04.688 --> 01:06.107
It's between you and me.

01:06.191 --> 01:08.359
A secret forever it shall be.

01:09.652 --> 01:12.906
- Secret forever,
cross my heart.

01:12.989 --> 01:14.282
What's my first task?

01:14.365 --> 01:16.117
I can't wait.
I'm so excited.

01:16.201 --> 01:17.952
I'm gonna be
the best minion ever.

01:18.036 --> 01:21.664
Oh, wait,
do I blog about this?

01:21.748 --> 01:22.832
- No.

01:24.793 --> 01:28.296
You can't talk about
this with anyone.

01:28.379 --> 01:30.548
For starters, I need
information about Daniel.

01:30.632 --> 01:31.549
He's broken up with Emma--

01:31.633 --> 01:33.009
- I know.

01:33.092 --> 01:35.261
I already blogged
about that last week.

01:35.345 --> 01:36.679
Don't you read my blog?

01:36.763 --> 01:40.517
I published "The End of Demma"
and "Demma No More"

01:40.600 --> 01:43.061
and is "The Max the New Demma?"

01:43.144 --> 01:44.813
- You're confusing,
and you talk too fast.

01:44.896 --> 01:46.648
Stop.

01:46.731 --> 01:51.361
Now, tell me about Daniel.

01:51.444 --> 01:53.279
- There's so much to say.

01:53.363 --> 01:55.698
Let me pull his file.

01:55.782 --> 01:57.575
Daniel was born April 1st,
so he's an Aries.

01:57.659 --> 02:00.286
Very headstrong.

02:00.370 --> 02:02.539
He's captain of all the teams
at school, including,

02:02.622 --> 02:04.874
but not exclusive to,
swim team, baseball team,

02:04.958 --> 02:06.584
basketball team, soccer team--

02:08.252 --> 02:09.545
- Em, it's me, I--

02:09.628 --> 02:12.549
EMMA: No, go away!

02:12.632 --> 02:16.719
- Whoa, listen, I'm sorry
I was kinda hard on you

02:16.803 --> 02:17.846
about the whole
Daniel thing, but--

02:17.929 --> 02:20.723
EMMA: No, that's not it.

02:20.807 --> 02:23.017
- Then what is it?
EMMA: I don't wanna say.

02:25.478 --> 02:26.229
No!

02:26.312 --> 02:27.772
- Well, what's the matter?

02:27.856 --> 02:33.278
- It's just every time I tell
myself not to think of Daniel,

02:33.361 --> 02:34.946
the person in front of me...

02:36.656 --> 02:38.116
Turns into Daniel.

02:38.199 --> 02:41.244
- ANDI'S VOICE: What?
Now you're talking crazy, Em.

02:41.327 --> 02:41.369
- Ah!

02:44.998 --> 02:45.915
{\an8}<i>[upbeat pop music]</i>

02:45.999 --> 02:48.751
{\an8}<i>WOMAN: ♪ I cast a spell ♪</i>

02:48.835 --> 02:50.670
{\an8}<i>♪ It takes a hold of you ♪</i>

02:50.753 --> 02:52.255
{\an8}<i>♪ I see my dreams ♪</i>

02:52.338 --> 02:54.090
{\an8}<i>♪ And they're all</i>
<i>coming true ♪</i>

02:54.173 --> 02:55.091
{\an8}<i>♪ Come on ♪</i>

02:55.174 --> 02:56.092
{\an8}<i>♪ Let's go ♪</i>

02:56.175 --> 02:57.927
{\an8}<i>♪ You and me together ♪</i>

02:58.011 --> 02:59.554
{\an8}<i>♪ Look up ahead ♪</i>

02:59.637 --> 03:00.930
{\an8}<i>♪ There's a magical adventure ♪</i>

03:01.014 --> 03:03.433
{\an8}<i>♪ Every witch way ♪</i>

03:03.516 --> 03:05.101
{\an8}<i>♪ Ay-ay-ay-ay-ay ♪</i>

03:05.184 --> 03:05.768
<i>♪ I'm trying</i>
<i>every witch way ♪</i>

03:05.852 --> 03:08.438
<i>♪ Ay-ay-ay-ay-ay ♪</i>

03:08.521 --> 03:10.690
<i>♪ I'm going</i>
<i>every witch way ♪</i>

03:10.773 --> 03:12.734
<i>♪ Ay-ay-ay-ay-ay ♪</i>

03:12.817 --> 03:14.777
<i>♪ Every witch way ♪</i>

03:15.320 --> 03:20.116
{\an8}- Come on, Em, I brought you
your favorite breakfast pizza.

03:22.201 --> 03:24.787
{\an8}Cheese, eggs, blueberry,

03:24.871 --> 03:26.623
and mango salsa.

03:29.459 --> 03:31.961
Emma, you can't hide
under there forever.

03:32.045 --> 03:33.379
EMMA: Watch me.

03:33.463 --> 03:35.798
- That's it,
it's tough love time.

03:37.759 --> 03:40.386
[gasps]

03:40.470 --> 03:42.639
We are going out now.

03:42.722 --> 03:46.142
I'm not gonna let you rot in
this pizza-filled dungeon.

03:50.563 --> 03:52.482
- I guess I should get out.

03:52.565 --> 03:53.816
I've just been--

03:53.900 --> 03:57.070
- I know, and it's probably
been harder for you

03:57.153 --> 03:58.655
with your condition.

03:58.738 --> 04:00.323
But you gotta keep living.

04:00.406 --> 04:01.783
- Thanks, Andi.

04:03.743 --> 04:05.912
- Oh, but you
gotta shower first.

04:05.995 --> 04:07.330
- Okay, be right back.

04:07.413 --> 04:10.583
- And please brush your teeth,
like, two or three times.

04:15.922 --> 04:18.800
- Okay, who's next
on the revenge list?

04:18.882 --> 04:20.718
- How much longer do we have
to keep practicing your spells?

04:20.802 --> 04:23.304
- As long as it takes for me
to get it right every time.

04:23.388 --> 04:24.931
So when I see
all these people tomorrow,

04:25.014 --> 04:28.226
I know my spells will work.

04:28.309 --> 04:29.811
Got a problem with that?

04:29.894 --> 04:32.146
- No.
Of course not.

04:32.230 --> 04:34.190
- Good.
Now who's next?

04:38.236 --> 04:39.237
- Gigi.

04:39.320 --> 04:40.863
What do you wanna
get Gigi back for?

04:40.947 --> 04:42.949
- All those photos she posted
of my mom and Principal Alonso

04:43.032 --> 04:45.743
when they were in love.

04:45.827 --> 04:47.996
Now, do your best Gigi.

04:48.079 --> 04:49.288
- Do I have to?

04:49.372 --> 04:51.958
- It helps me focus
and get it right!

04:53.293 --> 04:57.046
- "This is Gigi Rueda,
and I'm Miss Information."

04:57.130 --> 04:59.257
- For this girl, my only wish

04:59.340 --> 05:01.426
is that she can only
speak gibberish.

05:03.678 --> 05:07.140
Well?

05:07.223 --> 05:11.394
- [speaking gibberish]

05:11.477 --> 05:13.563
- Yes, I'm on a roll.

05:13.646 --> 05:15.231
Who's next?

05:17.984 --> 05:19.861
- Oh, I got Andi.

05:20.987 --> 05:23.364
"Oh, come on, what
you come at me for?"

05:25.783 --> 05:28.911
- Since she wants to become
a lion, tiger, or a whale,

05:28.995 --> 05:30.413
give this girl
her very own tail.

05:33.332 --> 05:35.918
- [gasps] My very own tail!

05:36.002 --> 05:37.920
And it matches my outfit.

05:41.007 --> 05:44.761
- Oh, I can't wait
for school tomorrow.

05:44.844 --> 05:45.470
- [speaking gibberish]

05:49.432 --> 05:50.808
- I really thought
you'd be better

05:50.892 --> 05:52.268
at all those carnival games--

05:52.351 --> 05:54.312
you know, from playing
videogames and stuff so much.

05:54.395 --> 05:57.607
- I let you win, okay,
to cheer you up.

05:57.690 --> 05:59.067
- Uh-huh.

05:59.150 --> 05:59.859
Is that why you sprayed your
water gun at the game attendant

05:59.942 --> 06:01.444
when you lost?

06:01.527 --> 06:04.614
- He gave me a defective
spray gun, okay?

06:04.697 --> 06:07.283
I was just demonstrating
its low water pressure.

06:09.368 --> 06:10.995
Hey, Em, over here.

06:11.079 --> 06:12.371
- What's this?

06:12.455 --> 06:14.999
- Emma Alonso's custom-designed
ice cream sundae bar.

06:16.084 --> 06:18.044
- Andi, that is so sweet.

06:18.127 --> 06:20.713
- Hey, hey, don't ruin it.

06:20.797 --> 06:21.756
Now dig in.

06:21.839 --> 06:23.925
I'm gonna go check
on my goldfish.

06:24.008 --> 06:25.468
He doesn't look too well.

06:26.719 --> 06:28.721
- Diego, this is awesome.

06:28.805 --> 06:31.140
Thank you.

06:31.224 --> 06:32.600
- No problem.

06:32.683 --> 06:35.269
And I'm sorry to hear
about you and Daniel.

06:35.353 --> 06:37.355
- Thanks, Diego, that's--

06:37.438 --> 06:39.732
- You okay?

06:39.816 --> 06:40.983
Is it the sprinkles?

06:41.067 --> 06:42.276
Are they making you sick?

06:42.360 --> 06:43.027
Do you need the
Heimlich maneuver?

06:43.111 --> 06:45.404
- No, no, I'm okay.

06:45.488 --> 06:48.282
I'm just gonna go
eat this over there.

06:50.701 --> 06:52.036
- What--what's wrong?

06:52.120 --> 06:55.998
- Diego, he mentioned
you know who.

06:56.082 --> 06:58.501
- Oh, Diego, can't he just
man the sundae bar

06:58.584 --> 07:00.002
without opening his mouth?

07:00.086 --> 07:01.045
- It's not his fault.

07:01.129 --> 07:01.963
I shouldn't have
gotten out of bed.

07:02.046 --> 07:03.756
I should just go.

07:03.840 --> 07:05.091
- No.

07:05.174 --> 07:07.218
Ugh, I didn't wanna
have to do this,

07:07.301 --> 07:08.886
but you leave me with no choice.

07:08.970 --> 07:10.638
- Do what?

07:16.227 --> 07:19.397
<i>[techno music]</i>

07:19.480 --> 07:21.482
- [laughing]

07:21.566 --> 07:25.611
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:25.695 --> 07:29.115
<i>[laughing]</i>

07:29.198 --> 07:30.116
- Daniel and Emma
just broke up.

07:30.199 --> 07:31.951
She shouldn't be laughing!

07:32.034 --> 07:32.952
[glass breaking]

07:33.035 --> 07:34.745
- Oh, my tablet!

07:34.829 --> 07:36.164
- Oh, relax.

07:37.832 --> 07:40.710
- Cool.

07:40.793 --> 07:43.838
- Now start boogering about
how much they miss each other.

07:43.921 --> 07:45.298
- Boogering?

07:45.381 --> 07:46.799
- Whatever it is you do
when you write stuff

07:46.883 --> 07:47.842
in that little scratchpad.

07:47.925 --> 07:49.635
- Blogging.

07:49.719 --> 07:52.054
- Oh, and you'll need video
footage of them crying about

07:52.138 --> 07:54.473
how much they miss each other.

07:54.557 --> 07:55.975
- Ah, I can fake all that.

07:56.058 --> 07:57.810
But I need footage of them
that I can doctor first.

07:57.894 --> 08:00.688
It's been really hard trying to
get either of them on camera.

08:05.151 --> 08:06.110
- What is this?

08:06.194 --> 08:10.072
- Headband...
slash hidden camera.

08:10.156 --> 08:11.824
- No way.

08:11.908 --> 08:13.201
This is the best day ever.

08:13.284 --> 08:14.827
- Now get on it.

08:14.911 --> 08:16.787
I've got props to
make for the play.

08:20.333 --> 08:21.083
- Those aren't...

08:21.167 --> 08:24.670
real, are they?

08:24.754 --> 08:26.005
- Of course they are.

08:26.088 --> 08:29.592
How can we expect to grab
the audience's attention

08:29.675 --> 08:31.052
unless the stakes--

08:31.135 --> 08:32.720
and the props--

08:32.803 --> 08:33.346
are real?

08:33.429 --> 08:36.933
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

08:37.015 --> 08:38.392
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:38.476 --> 08:41.102
- Okay, I can do this.

08:41.187 --> 08:43.563
Just don't think about not
thinking about Daniel.

08:48.236 --> 08:48.653
- What's your problem?

08:52.657 --> 08:54.408
{\an8}- [speaking foreign language]

09:00.456 --> 09:01.499
- Whoa.

09:01.582 --> 09:02.917
- Argh!

09:03.000 --> 09:04.418
- Are you okay?
- I'm fine.

09:04.502 --> 09:06.170
I'm just...

09:06.254 --> 09:07.630
Daniel?

09:07.713 --> 09:08.130
- Yeah?

09:08.214 --> 09:11.634
- Daniel Daniel?

09:11.717 --> 09:12.510
Daniel Miller Daniel?

09:12.593 --> 09:14.262
- Are you sure you're okay?

09:14.345 --> 09:17.515
- I'm--I'm--

09:17.598 --> 09:19.475
- She's fine, she's fine.

09:19.558 --> 09:22.019
Aren't you, Emma?
- I guess.

09:23.938 --> 09:25.690
Oh, that wasn't good.

09:25.773 --> 09:26.941
- [laughs] Are you kidding?

09:27.024 --> 09:30.111
Your "Daniel,
Daniel Miller Daniel?"

09:30.194 --> 09:32.154
Oh, it was great.

09:32.238 --> 09:33.197
- I wanted to come off cool,

09:33.281 --> 09:36.742
confident, totally together.

09:36.826 --> 09:38.452
- You did.

09:39.954 --> 09:43.291
Okay, just pretend like I've
just told you the funniest thing

09:43.374 --> 09:45.751
you've ever heard--

09:45.835 --> 09:48.754
like you couldn't care
less about Daniel.

09:49.422 --> 09:53.342
- [forced laughing]

09:53.426 --> 09:54.593
- Maybe I should go over
and talk to her,

09:54.677 --> 09:56.846
and make sure she's okay.

09:56.929 --> 09:58.180
What's she doing right now?

09:58.264 --> 10:01.267
- She's with Jax.
[Emma laughing shrilly]

10:01.350 --> 10:03.519
Oh, I think she just
swallowed a bug.

10:03.602 --> 10:06.314
Oh--oh, no, she's laughing.

10:06.397 --> 10:08.691
<i>Jax is making her laugh.</i>

10:08.774 --> 10:10.401
<i>- [laughing]</i>

10:23.372 --> 10:24.332
- Desdemona?

10:24.415 --> 10:25.333
- Argh!

10:25.416 --> 10:26.876
What are you doing here?

10:26.959 --> 10:29.086
I mean, how can I help you?

10:29.170 --> 10:30.713
- It's Daniel.

10:30.796 --> 10:33.507
- Ah-ha, and you wanna
get back together with him.

10:33.591 --> 10:34.633
- No.

10:34.717 --> 10:35.718
I mean yes.

10:35.801 --> 10:37.845
But I'm having a little...
problem.

10:37.928 --> 10:39.388
- Ah-ha, trying to find out
the best way

10:39.472 --> 10:41.057
to get back together with him?

10:41.140 --> 10:44.310
- No, it's--when I try not
to think about Daniel,

10:44.393 --> 10:46.062
the person in front of me

10:46.145 --> 10:49.440
becomes Daniel.

10:49.523 --> 10:52.943
- Ah, yes, the old broken
heart witch's curse.

10:53.027 --> 10:54.070
- This happens
to other witches?

10:54.153 --> 10:57.740
- Yes, especially after
their first big breakup.

10:57.823 --> 10:59.241
- Can you fix it?

11:01.702 --> 11:03.537
- I just did.

11:03.621 --> 11:05.581
But it won't be the end.

11:05.664 --> 11:07.792
As long as you
yearn after Daniel,

11:07.875 --> 11:10.419
you'll experience some...

11:10.503 --> 11:13.255
unique reactions.

11:13.339 --> 11:13.964
- How do I make them stop?

11:14.048 --> 11:16.133
- Easy.

11:16.217 --> 11:18.552
Get back together with Daniel.

11:18.636 --> 11:20.638
- He's so upset I lied to him.

11:20.721 --> 11:21.972
I don't think
he'll ever forgive me.

11:22.056 --> 11:27.561
- But you're star-crossed
lovers meant to be,

11:27.645 --> 11:29.480
just like Romeo and Jul--

11:30.981 --> 11:34.110
Hey, what would you say

11:34.193 --> 11:35.903
to playing Juliet?

11:35.986 --> 11:37.988
- Huh? Sophie's playing Juliet.

11:38.072 --> 11:39.824
- Oh, lead actresses
can always be benched

11:39.907 --> 11:41.200
with a sudden case of the flu.

11:41.283 --> 11:43.828
Or poison ivy.

11:43.911 --> 11:45.121
Or bubonic plague.

11:45.204 --> 11:45.871
- Desdemona!

11:45.955 --> 11:47.832
- [laughs] I'm kidding.

11:47.915 --> 11:50.584
But seriously,
I can replace her.

11:50.668 --> 11:52.628
I am the director.

11:52.711 --> 11:54.213
- I-I--

11:54.296 --> 11:56.132
No, I can't.

11:56.215 --> 11:56.757
There has to be another way.

11:58.926 --> 12:01.303
- Why don't you come
to rehearsal tonight?

12:01.387 --> 12:05.307
Once you see how great
and romantic the play is,

12:05.391 --> 12:07.893
you might change your mind.

12:07.977 --> 12:09.895
- I'll--I'll think about it.

12:09.979 --> 12:13.190
- Okay, but if you don't get
back together with Daniel soon,

12:13.274 --> 12:16.444
who knows what kind of
reaction you'll have next?

12:16.527 --> 12:17.653
- Like what?

12:17.736 --> 12:20.781
- Oh, just head to toe zits.

12:20.865 --> 12:23.492
A never-ending runny nose.

12:23.576 --> 12:25.453
Hair loss.

12:27.496 --> 12:29.165
That sort of thing.

12:29.248 --> 12:32.001
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

12:34.170 --> 12:35.880
- Diego, where are you?

12:35.963 --> 12:36.922
[gasps] Now's my chance.

12:39.884 --> 12:41.719
Revenge on Jax I still
haven't gotten.

12:41.802 --> 12:42.928
Turn the apple
he's eating rotten.

12:47.266 --> 12:49.143
[laughing]

12:50.519 --> 12:52.229
That's for making me
hop around school.

12:56.108 --> 12:58.110
[gasps]

12:58.194 --> 13:01.071
- [laughs]

13:01.155 --> 13:03.199
<i>[lively music]</i>

13:03.282 --> 13:05.618
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:05.701 --> 13:06.327
- [laughs]

13:06.410 --> 13:14.126
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:14.210 --> 13:16.879
- You should just give up
before this gets any uglier.

13:16.962 --> 13:18.047
- For you, maybe.

13:18.130 --> 13:20.341
How about some buns
for your hot dogs?

13:24.470 --> 13:26.180
- [laughs]

13:26.263 --> 13:28.057
You can't hide from me.

13:29.308 --> 13:30.392
[laughs]

13:30.476 --> 13:32.144
- Sorry I'm late, Maddie,
I was just--

13:32.228 --> 13:33.896
Maddie, what's going on?

13:35.147 --> 13:36.065
- Help me!

13:36.148 --> 13:37.566
- Oh, you want
some more popcorn?

13:37.650 --> 13:39.235
- No!

13:39.318 --> 13:42.363
[rushing wind]

13:46.325 --> 13:48.327
- What happened?

13:48.410 --> 13:51.288
Did Jax do that?

13:51.372 --> 13:52.456
- Did he do that?

13:52.540 --> 13:54.375
- He didn't do anything.

13:54.458 --> 13:56.001
I did.

13:58.170 --> 14:03.133
- I'd love to hear
an explanation as well.

14:03.217 --> 14:05.135
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

14:05.219 --> 14:08.597
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:09.390 --> 14:11.892
- I've seen food fights before,
but this--

14:11.976 --> 14:12.851
this is on another level!

14:12.935 --> 14:15.437
Where did all this
food come from?

14:15.521 --> 14:17.982
I mean, the cafeteria
doesn't even serve popcorn.

14:18.065 --> 14:20.276
- You mean you didn't
see us actually fighting?

14:20.359 --> 14:22.903
- No!

14:22.987 --> 14:25.114
But that doesn't mean I don't
know that the three of you

14:25.197 --> 14:26.240
are responsible.

14:26.323 --> 14:27.575
- You can't prove anything.

14:27.658 --> 14:30.411
- You are wearing the evidence.

14:30.494 --> 14:32.663
- Oh.
- We'll clean it up.

14:32.746 --> 14:33.581
- Yeah, and after that I
will see the three of you

14:33.664 --> 14:36.875
in detention for two weeks.

14:36.959 --> 14:39.795
- Wait, can't we
just negotiate this?

14:39.878 --> 14:41.463
- Yeah, you let Daniel do
the school play

14:41.547 --> 14:43.007
instead of detention.

14:43.090 --> 14:45.092
- You wanna help
with the play instead?

14:45.175 --> 14:46.427
Fine by me.

14:46.510 --> 14:48.971
- No, no, no, no, I was
just using it as an example.

14:49.054 --> 14:51.307
- Look, I will see the three
of you at 5:00 today

14:51.390 --> 14:53.851
in my office.

14:53.934 --> 14:57.438
Oh, and no food allowed.

14:57.521 --> 14:59.481
It actually doesn't taste
too bad, but--

15:05.654 --> 15:07.573
- You're a witch.

15:07.656 --> 15:09.325
- A wizard.

15:09.408 --> 15:10.492
What are you?

15:10.576 --> 15:12.911
- The last living Kanay.

15:12.995 --> 15:15.372
- Ugh, a Kanay?

15:15.456 --> 15:16.248
And you're friends with him?

15:16.332 --> 15:18.459
- I'd pick him over you any day.

15:18.542 --> 15:20.252
- You would?

15:20.336 --> 15:21.670
- Yes.

15:21.754 --> 15:23.005
Now let's get out of here.

15:23.088 --> 15:26.675
- Look, just because--
well, Jax is, like,

15:26.759 --> 15:29.261
new and mysterious

15:29.345 --> 15:33.015
and a really good swimmer
and all suave and stuff...

15:33.098 --> 15:34.892
- Don't make me change my mind.

15:34.975 --> 15:39.063
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

15:39.146 --> 15:40.648
- You won't believe
what just happened.

15:40.731 --> 15:44.276
I saw Emma in the hallway.

15:45.486 --> 15:47.196
- In the hallway!

15:47.279 --> 15:49.073
- How dare she!

15:49.156 --> 15:50.866
[laughs]

15:50.949 --> 15:52.534
- Very funny.

15:52.618 --> 15:54.119
You know who she was with?

15:54.203 --> 15:55.871
- Who's Andi for 300?

15:55.954 --> 15:59.416
- No, she was with
that new kid Jax.

16:00.542 --> 16:01.502
- That's it.

16:01.585 --> 16:03.045
I'm adding Jax to
the prank list.

16:06.298 --> 16:07.883
- Hey, thanks for helping me.

16:07.966 --> 16:09.927
I know...

16:10.010 --> 16:12.096
it's not easy.

16:12.179 --> 16:13.722
- I see him everywhere.

16:13.806 --> 16:16.266
So, hey, no big deal.

16:16.350 --> 16:20.604
- ♪ You killed my friend,
and now you're going to pay ♪

16:20.688 --> 16:24.149
♪ Either you or I
will join him today ♪

16:24.233 --> 16:27.569
- ♪ It will be you,
I'm sorry to say ♪

16:27.653 --> 16:29.279
- And cut.

16:29.363 --> 16:31.031
Spectacular, boys.

16:31.115 --> 16:33.409
♪ Just spectacular ♪

16:33.492 --> 16:35.911
Especially you, Daniel.

16:35.994 --> 16:38.372
So passionate.

16:38.455 --> 16:39.790
- Uh, thanks.

16:39.873 --> 16:42.751
- Oh, wait here, I've
got some new props for us.

16:45.254 --> 16:47.089
Here are our new props.

16:47.172 --> 16:48.924
- Are those real?

16:49.007 --> 16:49.925
- Yes.

16:50.008 --> 16:51.927
And so is the poison
at the end.

16:52.010 --> 16:54.638
I like my musicals real.

16:56.306 --> 17:00.144
- Coach Desdemona, I have some
more volunteers for the play.

17:02.771 --> 17:04.021
Wow, those swords,
they look real.

17:04.106 --> 17:05.357
Good job on the props.

17:05.441 --> 17:06.567
- Thank you.

17:06.650 --> 17:09.528
And of course they're real.
- What?

17:09.611 --> 17:11.946
You--you can't use real
swords for the play.

17:12.030 --> 17:12.906
- Why not?

17:12.990 --> 17:15.284
And don't say it's too violent.

17:15.367 --> 17:17.618
[whispering] The characters
die at the end.

17:17.703 --> 17:20.998
- Get new, fake swords.

17:21.080 --> 17:24.292
In the meantime, see what else
the props department may have.

17:25.711 --> 17:28.630
- Mm, amateurs.

17:28.714 --> 17:31.800
You heard the man.

17:31.884 --> 17:33.343
You, you--

17:34.595 --> 17:36.805
Go get me some swords
or something.

17:37.931 --> 17:40.434
And you, go help costumes girl.

17:40.517 --> 17:42.060
- You mean Katie?

17:42.144 --> 17:45.397
- I don't have time to remember
every single crew member's name.

17:45.481 --> 17:49.193
[snorting]

17:49.276 --> 17:51.653
Oh, okay, next scene.

17:51.737 --> 17:54.782
Sophie, Daniel, Pablo,
places, please.

17:58.494 --> 17:59.661
- [sneezing]

17:59.745 --> 18:00.662
- Are you okay?

18:00.746 --> 18:03.415
- Just a little--

18:03.499 --> 18:04.500
- Sophie, take five.

18:04.583 --> 18:07.169
- [sneezing]

18:07.252 --> 18:08.670
- Outside.

18:08.754 --> 18:09.588
- Should we all take a break?

18:09.671 --> 18:11.048
- Never.

18:11.131 --> 18:12.800
The show must go on

18:12.883 --> 18:16.261
and on and on--

18:16.345 --> 18:20.516
Emma, stand in for Sophie,
would you?

18:20.599 --> 18:22.643
- Oh, no, I don't--

18:22.726 --> 18:26.313
- Without a Juliet, we will
have to cancel the play.

18:26.396 --> 18:27.689
- It's just rehearsal.

18:27.773 --> 18:29.358
- This is theater.

18:29.441 --> 18:31.318
- Fine, I'll do it.

18:31.401 --> 18:32.736
Do you mind?

18:32.820 --> 18:34.112
- Whatever.

18:34.196 --> 18:35.447
- Okay.

18:35.531 --> 18:38.700
Romeo, Juliet, Tybalt--

18:38.784 --> 18:40.702
Where's my Tybalt?

18:40.786 --> 18:42.329
Pablo, where are you?

18:42.412 --> 18:43.539
- He just texted.

18:43.622 --> 18:45.541
[whispering]
He has the chicken pox.

18:45.624 --> 18:46.500
- [whispering] What?

18:47.626 --> 18:50.879
How am I gonna find
a replacement now?

18:50.963 --> 18:52.089
- I'll do it.

18:52.172 --> 18:53.298
- Perfect.

18:53.382 --> 18:54.925
Join the others on the stage.

18:56.301 --> 18:57.886
- We got 'em, we got 'em.

18:58.762 --> 19:00.889
- What are those?

19:00.973 --> 19:03.141
- Bread and salami from
the cafeteria kitchen.

19:03.225 --> 19:04.351
- Oh.

19:04.434 --> 19:05.602
All right,
it'll have to do for now.

19:05.686 --> 19:08.981
Hand them out.

19:09.064 --> 19:11.233
Emma, take a seat
while we rehearse

19:11.316 --> 19:14.444
with these new, um, swords.

19:16.530 --> 19:21.285
Okay, now Romeo fights
Tybalt to the death.

19:23.704 --> 19:26.290
- Ow.

19:26.373 --> 19:28.083
- Oops, sorry.

19:29.418 --> 19:32.421
<i>[energetic rock music]</i>

19:32.504 --> 20:40.197
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:40.280 --> 20:41.531
- I win.

20:41.615 --> 20:42.699
- No, I win.

20:42.783 --> 20:43.992
The salami is mightier
than the baguette.

20:44.076 --> 20:45.744
- Well, let's ask the audience.

20:45.827 --> 20:48.455
Emma?
<i>[music distorts, stops]</i>

20:48.538 --> 20:49.665
Emma?

20:57.547 --> 20:59.132
- That's the wrong end.

20:59.216 --> 21:00.467
- I know that.

21:03.220 --> 21:05.013
It's not working.

21:05.097 --> 21:07.307
- You have to push
harder than that.

21:09.601 --> 21:10.269
- Ow!

21:10.352 --> 21:12.646
Look what you made me do.

21:14.272 --> 21:16.149
- Ah!

21:16.233 --> 21:17.359
- What?

21:17.442 --> 21:18.068
- Your--

21:18.151 --> 21:20.904
your face, it's--

21:20.988 --> 21:22.280
- It's what?

21:22.364 --> 21:23.699
- It's purple.

21:23.782 --> 21:25.826
- [gasps]

21:30.914 --> 21:32.290
- What an insane day.

21:34.459 --> 21:36.378
[screams]

21:38.005 --> 21:40.090
I need to keep these things at
bay, turn 'em into birds,

21:40.173 --> 21:41.299
so they'll fly away.

21:41.383 --> 21:41.466
- Emma!

21:45.137 --> 21:46.722
Emma?

21:48.265 --> 21:51.226
{\an8}<i>[upbeat pop music]</i>

21:51.309 --> 21:58.317
{\an8}<i>♪ ♪</i>
